        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 529 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Topnot, or near Yanceyville, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Yanceyville...
Jericho...
Prospect Hill...
Leasburg...
Hamer...
Topnot...
and Hightowers.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for north central
North Carolina...and south central Virginia.</instruction>
